Field Marshal Fedor Von Bock (1880-1945)
He commanded Army Group North during the Invasion of Poland (1939). In 1940, he was assigned to command Army Group B during the invasion of France (1940). By 1941, after the successful campaigns of the previous years, Bock was given in the command of Army Group Center during Operation Barbarossa of 1941. He took responsibility for the failure of the final phase of Barbarossa codename Operation Typhoon the offensive to Moscow during winter of 1941.
